<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,404,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1088,1114]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Beltran &amp; M. Weigend" authorityYear="2014" box="[294,569,1088,1114]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laraosensis">
<emphasis box="[294,569,1088,1114]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Malesherbia laraosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique among Peruvian 
<taxonomicName box="[867,1009,1088,1114]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[867,1009,1088,1114]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Malesherbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its caespitose habit with very short branches (up to 
<quantity box="[319,389,1124,1151]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
long) and differs dramatically from all previously known Peruvian species with similar floral morphology, which are much larger (usually&gt; 
<quantity box="[667,738,1160,1187]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" unit="cm" value="50.0">50 cm</quantity>
tall) and branched mainly above. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardi" authorityYear="1961" box="[1131,1424,1160,1186]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arequipensis">
<emphasis box="[1131,1424,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Malesherbia arequipensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only other species that is similiarly small, but it is an annual or short-lived perennial with deeply and repeteadly pinnatisect leaves and white flowers. In floral colour and morphology 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Beltran &amp; M. Weigend" authorityYear="2014" box="[963,1132,1232,1258]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laraosensis">
<emphasis box="[963,1132,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">M. laraosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricardi (1965: 6)" authorityName="Ricardi" authorityPageNumber="6" authorityYear="1965" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">M. splendens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ricardi, S. M." box="[254,449,1268,1295]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="3 - 10" refId="ref2401" refString="Ricardi, S. M. (1965) Estudios en Malesherbiaceae II. Gayana Botanica 12: 3 - 10." type="journal article" year="1965">Ricardi (1965: 6)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gilg (1913: 11)" authorityName="Gilg" authorityPageNumber="11" authorityYear="1913" box="[505,868,1268,1294]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scarlatiflora">
<emphasis box="[505,684,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">M. scarlatiflora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gilg, E." box="[692,868,1268,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="11 - 12" refId="ref1913" refString="Gilg, E. (1913). Malesherbiaceae andinae. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 50 (2 - 3, Beibl. 111): 11 - 12." type="journal article" year="1913">Gilg (1913: 11)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but both species are ca. 
<quantity box="[1154,1198,1268,1295]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
tall, have long, ovateacuminate, densely villous leaves, and have longer sepals than petals. Conversely, the leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Beltran &amp; M. Weigend" authorityYear="2014" box="[1241,1408,1304,1330]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laraosensis">
<emphasis box="[1241,1408,1304,1330]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">M. laraosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are obovate, abaxially sericeous and adaxially subglabrous, with only few teeth on both sides, and the sepals and petals are more or less the same size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,404,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gilg" authorityYear="1913" box="[189,477,1412,1438]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scarlatiflora">
<emphasis box="[189,477,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Malesherbia scarlatiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only other species known from the area of the 
<typeStatus box="[1066,1114,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">type</typeStatus>
collection of 
<taxonomicName box="[1267,1444,1412,1438]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laraoesensis">
<emphasis box="[1267,1444,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">M. laraoesensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on phytogeography and morphology the new species appears to belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="sect. Malesherbia" box="[1070,1423,1448,1475]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Malesherbia">
<emphasis box="[1070,1212,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Malesherbia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1281,1423,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Malesherbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a group centred in Central 
<collectingCountry box="[416,471,1485,1511]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="286" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,404,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,1520,1546]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Distribution:</emphasis>
—The new species is so far only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[906,954,1521,1547]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">type</typeStatus>
locality in Laraos, an area with little human intervention.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,404,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,420,1592,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Habitat and ecology:</emphasis>
—Soils are calcareous and vegetation is dominated by shrubs of 
<taxonomicName box="[1078,1235,1592,1619]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1078,1186,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Baccharis</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz &amp; Pavon (1798: 28)" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityPageNumber="28" authorityYear="1798" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Columelliaceae" genus="Columellia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bruniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obovata">
<emphasis box="[1243,1451,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Columellia obovata</emphasis>
Ruiz &amp; Pavón (1798:28)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Harling (1992: 16)" authorityName="Harling" authorityPageNumber="16" authorityYear="1992" box="[410,784,1628,1655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jungia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schuerae">
<emphasis box="[410,584,1628,1654]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Jungia schuerae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harling, G." box="[590,784,1628,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="16 - 18" refId="ref2108" refString="Harling, G. (1992). Two new species of Jungia (Compositae) from Peru. Novon 2: 16 - 18. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 3391601" type="journal article" year="1992">Harling (1992:16)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Arroyo (1976: 50)" authorityName="Arroyo" authorityPageNumber="50" authorityYear="1976" box="[794,1167,1628,1655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fiebrigii">
<emphasis box="[794,976,1628,1654]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Fabiana fiebrigii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Arroyo, S." box="[980,1167,1628,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="49 - 54" refId="ref1756" refString="Arroyo, S. (1976) Novedades en el genero Fabiana (Solanaceae). Hickenia 1 (10): 49 - 54." type="journal article" year="1976">Arroyo (1976:50)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="H. Beltran &amp; A. Galan (1998: 168)" authorityName="H. Beltran &amp; A. Galan" authorityPageNumber="168" authorityYear="1998" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="larahuinensis">
<emphasis box="[1218,1452,1628,1654]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Senecio larahuinensis</emphasis>
H. Beltrán &amp; A. Galan (1998:168)
</taxonomicName>
, and herbaceous species, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz &amp; Pavon (1798: 26)" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityPageNumber="26" authorityYear="1798" box="[855,1335,1664,1691]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Salvia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oppositiflora">
<emphasis box="[855,1063,1664,1690]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Salvia oppositiflora</emphasis>
Ruiz &amp; Pavón (1798:26)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,404,1835]" box="[189,926,1700,1727]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,323,1700,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Phenology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Beltran &amp; M. Weigend" authorityYear="2014" box="[351,628,1700,1726]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malesherbiaceae" genus="Malesherbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laraosensis">
<emphasis box="[351,628,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Malesherbia laraosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers from May to July.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,404,1835]" box="[189,1109,1736,1763]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,343,1736,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Ethymology:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3329334301" box="[372,1106,1736,1763]" location="Laraos District" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" specimenCount="1">
The species name refers to the 
<typeStatus box="[718,766,1737,1763]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">type</typeStatus>
locality in the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:9C5787AADA50054493B0FADCE33FF8D1:11216067DA500544909EFCF8E36BF919" box="[934,1106,1736,1763]" name="Laraos District" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Laraos District</location>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,404,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,437,1772,1798]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—According to the Red List criteria of 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[888,1041,1772,1798]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" refId="ref2146" refString="IUCN. (2001) Categorias y Criterios de la Lista Roja de la IUCN. Version 3.1. Preparado por la comision de Supervivencia de Especies de la IUCN. Gland, Suiza y Cambridge, Reino Unido, ii + 33 pp." type="book" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, the species should be included into the category “not evaluated” (NE), since it is only known from a single locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
